Showa Shell Sekiyu K.K. (Showa Shell) is an independent energy company, which carries out crude oil procurement, refining and sale of refined oil products. It also sells propane gas, lubricants and electricity. Its product portfolio includes gasoline, diesel, heavy oil, xylene, benzene, propylene, butane and heating oil. Showa Shell also produces and markets liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) products and special products such as clean butane, clean auto, bitumen, compounds for construction material, and fuel and lubricants for jets and vessels. It also operates in the solar sector through a portfolio of panels and systems. Showa Shell is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.The company's strategic intent is to expand its business portfolio in the solar energy sector. In line with this approach, the company started the construction of a mega solar plant in Nakagawa, Japan.Showa Shell Sekiyu K.K. (5002) - Clean Technology - Deals and Alliances Profile provides you comprehensive data and trend analysis of the company's Mergers and Acquisitions (M&As), partnerships and financings. The report provides detailed information on Mergers and Acquisitions, Equity/Debt Offerings, Private Equity, Venture Financing and Partnership transactions recorded by the company over a five year period. The report offers detailed comparative data on the number of deals and their value categorized into deal types, sub-sector and regions.GlobalData derived the data presented in this report from proprietary in-house Clean Technology eTrack deals database, and primary and secondary research.ScopeFinancial Deals - Analysis of the company's financial deals including Mergers and Acquisitions, Equity/Debt Offerings, Private Equity, Venture Financing and Partnerships.Deals by Year - Chart and table displaying information encompassing the number of deals and value reported by the company by year, for a five year period.Deals by Type - Chart and table depicting information including the number of deals and value 